\begin_layout Standard
This memo suggests some changes to constants used frequently in the code
 and in the old descriptions of Bulletin 9.
 Most of these are not significant, but it would still be useful to update
 and standardize what is used.
 For example, different formulas use different constants in place of the
 gas constant for dry air, with different numbers of significant digits,
 and the result is that sometimes results are inconsistent.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*

\emph on
